task.summary: Made changes so there's a main page now with some basic images on it. Most of the edited stuff is just commenting out code so it will work for you locally.

I was able to build a local database for all the data coming from the website linked. I did get the front end to pull the data from the MySQL database and display it on the web page. I needed to "npm install axios" for fetching the data and "npm install node-cron" for making the data tables update (I set the increment to 2 minutes) . Like Rain said, there is data for all the garages since the data was there for them in the site I used it all, but we can take out Amelia Paramore and Rosen lot if we want. As of now the front shows the all 9. for the tables, I set the primary id to be an AUTO_INCREMENT in, but used api location id as a UNIQUE KEY. I'm gonna put a .sql export in the root folder of the project if anyone wants to import a their table to look like mine and use the functions mine uses. I have not touched anything else about the migrating the garage status to the home page or the google maps issue or the OAUTH thing.
